            },
            "answer_text": "She has PTSD. She appears to have no sensory issues and never melts down in public. She doesn't mask as neurotypical. When we meet her she is fourteen, an age at which you mask like your life depends on it. Let's face it, it probably does. She got angry once. Her actress interpreted it as making her soft voice slightly sharper. Autistic symptoms become clearer under stress. Seeing her mother die would have made her neurotic and anxious if she were autistic. Instead she is the calmest, most relaxed person ever. I don't know if this is \"symptomatic\" of neurotypicality, but I am pretty sure she's not autistic. ",
